title: Shannon on Eagles pulling Hurts against Washington, 'What the hell was that?' | NFL | UNDISPUTED
tags: fox|fox sports|fs1|fox sports 1|undisputed|skip bayless|shannon sharpe|skip and shannon|fs1 undisputed|skip|bayless|shannon|sharpe|sports|news|nfl|football|week 17|nfl week 17|philadelphia|eagles|doug pederson|jalen hurts|carson wentz|washington|playoff|nfc east|react|Nate Sudfeld|Philadelphia Eagles|Hurts|Washington Football Team|Jalen Hurts NFL|Philadelphia Eagles NFL|Eagles NFL|Nate Sudfeld NFL
description: The Philadelphia Eagles took a 14-20 lead over Washington last night, then it was all downhill for Philly after that. After a failed 4th-and-goal attempt, Doug Pederson yanked Jalen Hurts for Nate Sudfeld who turned it over twice and finished with just 32 passing yards on 5-of-12 passing. Pederson said after the game that he was quote 'coaching to win.'
